cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a method for object detection using R-CNN and focuses on weakly-supervised extractive rationale generation. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method for learning to unfold latent discriminative part configurations of object instances automatically and simultaneously in detection without using any supervision for part configurations. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a folding-unfolding method to train the AOG and convolutional networks end-to-end. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper proposes an AOGParsing operator to substitute the RoIPooling operator widely used in R-CNN. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Not applicable.
